      "content": "Your concerns about your gut are completely understandable, but you're missing the bigger picture here. The infection isn't *gone* until every single last microbe is dead, and stopping early is a recipe for a relapse that will be far worse. You need to finish the full course, and if you're worried about the gut, you can take a high-quality probiotic *after* you finish the antibiotics. Stick to the prescription; it's the only way to guarantee a complete cure.",
